.TH PKGMAN-DSEARCH 8 "PKGMAN-#VERSION# Manual"

.SH NAME
pkgman-dsearch \- search the repositories for package name/description

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pkgman dsearch
.B [-v|-vv] [--path]
.B [--regex]
.I EXPR

.SH DESCRIPTION
Search the repositories for \fIEXPR\fR in packages' name/description.
.br
It looks in all directories specified in \fC/etc/pkgman.conf\fR.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v
Show version in the listing.
.TP
.B \-vv
Show version and description in the listing.
.TP
.B \-\-path
Show package source path in the listing.
.TP
.B \-\-regex
Interpret \fIEXPR\fR as regular expression.
.TP
.I EXPR
String or regular expression.

